## Frontend (React/TypeScript)

### Pseudo-path convention

Use a special sentinel path: `trash:///` — this is not a real filesystem path, so it won't collide with any real directory. The FileBrowser detects this path and switches to "trash mode."

### Files to modify

**`src/api/trash.ts`** (new) — API client functions:
```ts
listTrash()           → GET /trash/list
restoreItem(name)     → POST /trash/restore
deleteTrashItem(name) → DELETE /trash/<name>
emptyTrash()          → DELETE /trash
```

**`src/store/slices/trashSlice.ts`** (new) — Redux slice:
- State: `items: TrashEntry[]`, `status`
- Thunks: `listTrashThunk`, `restoreItemThunk`, `deleteTrashItemThunk`, `emptyTrashThunk`
- `TrashEntry` type: `{ name, original_path, deleted_at, type, size }`

**`src/store/index.ts`** — Register `trash` reducer

**`src/store/slices/fileSystemSlice.ts`** — `deleteFileThunk` and `deleteDirThunk` remain unchanged (they still call `DELETE /fs/file` and `DELETE /fs/dir`), but those backend endpoints now trash instead of hard-delete. No frontend changes needed here.

**`src/components/files/PlacesPanel.tsx`**:
- Add a hardcoded "Trash" entry in the default places section (after Home and Root)
- On click, navigate to `trash:///` pseudo-path
- Active state detection: check if current path is `trash:///`

**`src/components/files/Breadcrumbs.tsx`**:
- When `currentPath === 'trash:///'`: show "Trash" label with Trash2 icon, no editable path, no breadcrumb segments
- Clicking the bar in trash mode should NOT enter edit mode (no path to edit)

**`src/components/files/FileBrowser.tsx`** — Main changes:
- Detect `currentPath === 'trash:///'` as trash mode
- In trash mode:
  - Load items via `listTrashThunk` instead of `listDirThunk`
  - Map `TrashEntry[]` to `FileEntry[]` for rendering compatibility
  - Show different context menu (Restore, Delete Permanently — no Rename, Copy, etc.)
  - Show "Empty Trash" button in toolbar
  - Disable drag-and-drop upload
  - Disable New Folder button
  - Disable paste
- Double-click in trash mode: no-op (don't navigate into trashed dirs)

**`src/components/files/FileContextMenu.tsx`**:
- Accept a `trashMode` prop
- In trash mode, show only: Restore, Delete Permanently (destructive), Properties

**`src/components/files/Toolbar.tsx`**:
- Accept a `trashMode` prop
- In trash mode: hide New Folder/Upload, show "Empty Trash" button, show "Restore" for selected items

**`src/components/files/DeleteConfirmDialog.tsx`**:
- Update the dialog text: when in trash mode, say "permanently delete" instead of "move to trash"
- When not in trash mode, update text to say "Move to Trash" instead of "Delete" (since it's now a soft delete)

